(18, 'Overview of Self-Checkout', 'assets/images/module/module_default/default.png', 'Chapter 1 of NCR 7340 Self-Checkout Store Manager\\''s Guide', '<h1><strong>Introduction</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<div>NCR Self-Checkout permits shoppers to checkout on their own.&nbsp;Shoppers can scan, bag, and pay without assistance, permitting&nbsp;checkout staff to provide customer service in other areas.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The following list includes some of the NCR Self-Checkout features:</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NCR Self-Checkout&rsquo;s ergonomic design brings all elements within easy reach of the shopper, which speeds scanning, bagging, and final payment.</li>\r\n	<li>The NCR 7401 touchscreen serves as the self-checkout consumer interface. Shoppers use the touchscreen to guide them through their transaction. A tri-light notifies store personnel when assistance is needed.</li>\r\n	<li>The NCR 7875 Bi-Optic AR Scanner reads five sides of a product, accepting almost any orientation. This means cakes or meat can be scanned without turning them over. After a product is scanned, the price is called out and displays on the screen.</li>\r\n	<li>Depending on your unit, NCR Self-Checkout can accept cash or cards. Shoppers can use a debit or credit card for payment, use coupons, or, with the cash module, pay with cash and coins.</li>\r\n	<li>NCR Self-Checkout has security features to help prevent shrinkage. The closed circuit video camera plays back transactions on the screen, reminding shoppers that they are being monitored. A weight displacement sensor identifies when an item that has not been scanned is added to the bagging area. Security software further identifies inconsistencies in scanning and bagging.</li>\r\n	<li>NCR Self-Checkout has several optional features for providing customer service. For instance, a Remote Approval Station permits store personnel to view and monitor the activity on multiple checkout lanes from one location and it permits shoppers to pay for their transactions by check. The in-store pager provides store personnel with immediate&nbsp;notification when the self-checkout&nbsp;system requires attention.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>NCR 7340 Self-Checkout Lanes</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<div>NCR 7340 Self-Checkout has two lane styles:</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Self-Checkout Lane &ndash; designed to enable shoppers to checkout on their own. The Self-Checkout Lane style may or may not include a cash module for accepting bills and coins for payment. In addition, the Self-Checkout Lane may be configured with a basket shelf for&nbsp;express orders, or an input belt to accommodate larger orders.</li>\r\n	<li>Convertible Lane &ndash; designed to serve as both a self-checkout and a cashier-assisted lane. This lane can be converted to the desired mode whenever customer traffic or labor issues dictate.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>Both lane styles have similar functionality and components. Your store&nbsp;may have one of these lane styles, or both.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The following sections show illustrations of the two styles of NCR Self- Checkout terminals. Please refer to these illustrations to locate the various components discussed in this manual.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Self-Checkout Lane with Cash Module</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<div><img alt=\\"Self-Checkout Lane with Cash Module 1 Self Checkout\\" src=\\"http://192.168.233.133/ssco_mbl/temp/01.png\\" style=\\"width: 537px; height: 519px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; margin: 10px;\\" /></div>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Self-Checkout Lane &ndash; Credit/Debit Only</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<div><img alt=\\"Self-Checkout Lane  Credit/Debit Only\\" src=\\"http://192.168.233.133/ssco_mbl/temp/02.png\\" style=\\"width: 536px; height: 621px; margin: 10px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;\\" /></div>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong><span style=\\"line-height: 1.2;\\">Self-Checkout Lane with Input Belt</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<div><img alt=\\"Self-Checkout Lane  Credit/Debit Only\\" src=\\"http://192.168.233.133/ssco_mbl/temp/03.png\\" style=\\"width: 543px; height: 469px; margin: 10px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;\\" /></div>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Convertible Lane</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<div><img alt=\\"Self-Checkout Lane  Credit/Debit Only\\" src=\\"http://192.168.233.133/ssco_mbl/temp/04.png\\" style=\\"width: 544px; height: 467px; margin: 10px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;\\" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Remote Approval Station</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<div>The optional Remote Approval (RAP) Station is able to control and monitor up to 12 self-checkout terminals at a given time. Although the self-checkout terminal enables customers to perform their own checkouts, intervention from store personnel is sometimes required. The RAP Station permits store personnel to intervene from a remote location.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><br />\r\nThe RAP Station operates through the optional Remote Approval Program. The RAP Station operates with a touchscreen for ease of use. Once signed on, store personnel have access to information on any of the self-checkout terminals that are configured. The Remote Approval Program:</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Notifies store personnel when an exception has been encountered&nbsp;at any of the self-checkout terminals.</li>\r\n	<li>Provides store personnel the ability to see both the online receipt and all outstanding exceptions (including their severity) for any of the configured self-checkout terminals.</li>\r\n	<li>Permits store personnel to view video of the activity of four selfcheckout&nbsp;lanes together at one time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The video receipt on the RAP station displays in journal format. A new line appears on the video receipt when items are modified or voided at the self-checkout lane. All exceptions related to the transaction in progress are added as lines within the scrolling receipt so that store personnel can determine when and why they occurred. Audio feedback is also supported at the RAP station in the form of beeps and other tones.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>In most cases, store personnel can approve or override the exceptions at any time, while the customer continues with their transaction. In some cases, manual intervention at the self-checkout terminal itself may be required. Exceptions can also be handled by category (security, restricted items, coupons, and so forth) or in some cases, they may be approved or overridden collectively.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>The RAP Station may include a standard point of sale terminal so that transactions can be transferred from the self-checkout lane to the RAP Station. This permits a self-checkout customer to pay with additional tenders, such as checks or food stamps.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Refer to the module NCR 7340 Self-Checkout Remote Approval Station Operator&rsquo;s Guide for detailed information on installing and using the Remote Approval Program. Below is an illustration of a sample RAP Station configuration.</div>\r\n\r\n<div><img alt=\\"Self-Checkout Lane  Credit/Debit Only\\" src=\\"http://192.168.233.133/ssco_mbl/temp/05.png\\" style=\\"width: 550px; height: 397px; margin: 10px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;\\" /></div>\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Using SCOT Terminals</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Shoppers</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Self-Checkout Procedure</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<div>Using the SCOT terminal for self-checkout is very simple.</div>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Scan or weigh an item and then place the item in the bag located on&nbsp;the bag well.</li>\r\n	<li>After scanning all items, press the Finish and Pay button.</li>\r\n	<li>Follow the instructions for completing payment method that&nbsp;display on the screen.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Common Shopper Mistakes</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<div>Though using the SCOT terminal is easy, there are a few things customers often do that cause security errors in the transaction. Being aware of these common mistakes will enable you to quickly identify the cause of transaction problems and help shoppers become more efficient SCOT users.</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Placing any item (such as a purse) on the set aside shelf next to the terminal screen will cause a weight error. The set aside shelf is part of the bag well and security scale. When the system detects weight placed on the security scale it verifies the weight against the last item scanned.</li>\r\n	<li>Removing items from the bag well area before transaction is completed changes the weight on the scale and causes a security error.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Store Personnel</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<div>Store personnel are responsible for:</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Monitoring activity on the SCOT terminals.</li>\r\n	<li>Assisting customers with their transactions, when needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Keeping each SCOT terminal well stocked with money, receipt paper, and shopping bags.</li>\r\n	<li>Resolving problems such as paper and coin jams, or scanner issues.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>The next chapters will provide store personnel with the information&nbsp;needed to perform these tasks.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n');

